definitions.definition: Willing to act dishonestly for personal gain; accepting bribes .
In a depraved state; debased ; perverted ; morally degenerate ; weak in morals .
examples: The government here is corrupt , so we'll emigrate to escape them.

definitions.definition: Abounding in errors ; not genuine or correct ; in an invalid state.
examples: The text of the manuscript is corrupt .
It turned out that the program was corrupt - that's why it wouldn't open.

definitions.definition: In a putrid state; spoiled ; tainted ; vitiated ; unsound .
